<font color="#FF0000">GI BENEFITS FOR SPATZ</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jul 29 12:26:54 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
GI Benefits for Spatz<br><br>
Spatz, I've answered you above, but once more for you to understand.<br><br>
I did not go back because the war was no longer being fought to win. <br>
Because individuals, like you had weaken this nation from within. <br>
Because, this great nation turned its back not only on its military men but also on the Vietnamese to whom we had promised so much. <br>
Because we abandon millions of Vietnamese to communist subversion and dominion. <br>
All because gutless politicians were too afraid of the giants in this promised land, because they listened to people like you, who were wise and knew what was right for this nation. The spies, that looked over the Vietnam issue and  came back with all type of reports and excuses why we should not be there. Why the war was not right for AMERICA and so, we called for a cease-fire and we stopped firing, but the Communist never stopped firing.<br>
They continued to destroy villages, to kill innocent children, women and old men. Why? <br>
So that the NVA soldier promised, a piece of land in South Vietnam would claim his part of the spoils of war. So that he could claim his GI benefits. Perhaps if you showed them your credentials Spatz, they might have set a piece of land aside for you.<br><br>
 Face, it Spatz in the final analysis you lost, we all lost. We lost our pride, honor, and all that pertains to what made us great. What a new Spatz humanitarian principle, To abandoned the Vietnamese to a sorrowful destiny. You speak about saving lives, didn't they count? You also never answered me. How many bedpans would you have washed to save a Vietnamese child? I would have kept firing, but you; you wanted your GI benefits.<br><br>
Now that is one thing I would have opposed, GI benefits for Conscientious Objectors. What a disgrace for the war veteran, that would have been. You wanted the glory Spatz, but was not willing to pay the real price of war.<br><br>

